A fusion of historical drama and mystery, this provocative new series focuses on the effects of World War II on the villages of England&#039;s vulnerable southern coast. As the war heats up in Europe, police inspector Christopher Foyle (Michael Kitchen, "Reckless", "Our of Africa") is prevented from enlisting by his superiors who need his talent at home. Foyle is an everyday detective, waging war against local crime in an atmosphere suffused with extraordinary personal and social turmoil.
